## Expected Metrics
- **RTO (Recovery Time Objective)**: Target under 15 minutes
- **RPO (Recovery Point Objective)**: Based on DynamoDB Global Tables replication lag (typically seconds)
- **Health check latency**: Route 53 failover detection within 30-60 seconds
- **Validation success rate**: All endpoint health checks returning 200 OK
- **Data consistency**: S3 replication status showing COMPLETED for all objects

## Rollback Triggers
- Health check failures exceeding threshold (e.g., 3 consecutive failures)
- Application endpoint returning 5xx errors
- Database write failures or replication lag over 60 seconds
- SSM Automation validation step failure
- Manual override trigger via Systems Manager

## Audit Trail
- CloudTrail: All API calls logged with IAM principal identity
- EventBridge: State machine execution events captured
- S3 Access Logs: Object access and replication status
- CloudWatch Logs: Application-level validation results
- AWS Config: Configuration change history for compliance

